The paper focuses on developing a federated meta-learning framework for recommendation systems, which involves machine learning techniques for sharing information among users while preserving user privacy. This work is primarily related to the field of machine learning, specifically in the areas of recommender systems, meta-learning, and federated learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also involves data science (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with user-specific recommendation models and sharing information among users.
